{{wikipedia}}
{{wikispecies|Taxus}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|ew}}, from {{inh|en|ang|īw}}, {{m|ang|ēow}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*īwaz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*īhwaz}} (compare {{cog|is|yr|ýr}}), masculine variant of {{m|gem-pro|*īwō}} (compare {{cog|nl|ijf}}, {{cog|de|Eibe}}), from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*h₁eyHweh₂}}.
See also {{cog|hit||tr=eja||type of evergreen|sc=Xsux}}, {{cog|cy|yw||yews}}, {{cog|ga|sga|eo}} [both cognates of {{cog|ang|īw}}, {{cog|ang|ēow}}]; and {{cog|ltg|īva||bird cherry}}, {{cog|lt|ievà||bird cherry}}, {{cog|ru|и́ва||willow}}.<ref>Marlies Philippa et al., eds., ''Etymologisch Woordenboek van het Nederlands'', A-Z, s.v. “ijf” (Amsterdam UP, 3 Dec. 2009). [http://www.etymologie.nl]</ref>
====Pronunciation====
* {{enPR|yo͞o}}, {{IPA|en|/juː/|/jɪʊ̯/}}
* {{rhymes|en|uː|s=1}}
* {{homophones|en|ewe|u|you|hew}} {{qualifier|in h-dropping dialects}}, [[hue]] {{qualifier|in h-dropping dialects}}
====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} A species of coniferous tree, ''[[Taxus baccata]]'', with dark-green flat needle-like leaves and seeds bearing red [[aril]]s, native to western, central and southern Europe, northwest Africa, northern Iran and southwest Asia.
#: {{syn|en|{{vern|English yew}}|{{vern|European yew}}|{{vern|common yew}}}}
# {{lb|en|countable|by extension}} Any [[tree]] or [[shrub]] of the genus ''[[Taxus]]''.
# Other conifers resembling plants in genus ''[[Taxus]]''
## in family [[Podocarpaceae]]
## in family [[Cephalotaxaceae]]
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[wood]] of the such trees.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1786|passage=To prevent a too great [[consumption]] of [[yew]], [[bowyer]]s were directed to make four [[bow]]s of [[witch-hazel]], [[ash]] or [[elm]], to one of [[yew]], and no person under [[seventeen]] [[year]]s of age, unless [[possess]]ed of [[moveable]]s worth [[forty]] [[mark]]s, of the son of [[parent]]s having an [[estate]] of [[ten]] [[pound]]s [[per annum]] might [[shoot]] in an [[yew]] bow, under a [[penalty]] of 6s. 8d.|author=Francis Grose|title=A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons|page=37}}
# A [[bow]] for [[archery]], made of yew wood.
